# World Cup 2026 Betting App

## Your role
You are a senior software engineer. Keep solutions simple, pragmatic, and well-explained. Prefer the smallest change that solves the problem. Reuse existing patterns before introducing new ones.

---

## What this app is (product intent ‚Äî do not change without owner approval)
A private, invite-only score-prediction game for FIFA World Cup 2026 (Jun 11 ‚Äì Jul 19, 2026). Approved users predict match scores and tournament outcomes and compete on a live leaderboard. The admin approves registrations and recalculates scores. The app is shared with a small group of friends ‚Äî **not a public product**.

It must be:
- Free to host (Vercel + Supabase free tiers ‚Äî no paid Node host).
- Installable as a PWA on iOS and Android.
- Bilingual (English + Hebrew with full RTL).
- Strict on rate limits ‚Äî worldcup26.ir may return 429. The serverless `/api/football/*` layer caches games for 30 s (teams longer) and uses single-flight de-dupe to stay polite.

---

## Stack ‚Äî Vercel + Supabase only
- **Frontend:** React 19 + Vite 7 + Mantine v8, deployed to **Vercel**.
- **Database:** **Supabase** (Postgres). Tables: `users`, `predictions`, `prediction_edits`, `matches_mirror`, `teams_mirror`, `tournament_bonus` (and any others added via migrations).
- **Backend logic:** Vercel **Serverless Functions** under `/api/*`. Do **not** use Railway or any other Node host ‚Äî keep hosting to Vercel + Supabase only, free of charge.
- **External APIs:** [worldcup26.ir](https://worldcup26.ir/api-docs/) (WC 2026 fixtures + live scores; optional JWT service account kept server-side), Resend (email, optional).
- Secrets live in Vercel env vars. The browser only sees `VITE_*` public vars.
- Passwords hashed with **bcryptjs** (pure JS ‚Äî `bcrypt` native binary breaks on Vercel).
- Auth is **JWT** (7-day expiry), signed server-side, stored in an **HttpOnly `wc_session` cookie**. `serverApi` uses `withCredentials: true`. A non-sensitive UI cache `wc_user` lives in `localStorage`.

## Mobile / PWA
This is a **React web app, not React Native**. It must be installable as a **PWA** so users can "Add to Home Screen" on iOS and Android. Required: web manifest, `vite-plugin-pwa` service worker, iOS `apple-touch-icon` + `apple-mobile-web-app-*` meta tags, and 192/512 px maskable icons.

## Hebrew language support (i18n)
The app must support Hebrew. Use a single i18n layer (`react-i18next`) with `en` and `he` translations. Set `<html dir="rtl" lang="he">` when locale is Hebrew. All user-facing strings come from translation keys ‚Äî never hard-code text in components.

## Data fetching strategy
Football fixtures only change between stages, not during them. Therefore:
- **One API call per stage** (Group Stage, R32, R16, QF, SF, Third Place, Final). Cache the result client-side (`useMatches`) until the stage advances.
- **Never refetch the full schedule on route change.**
- worldcup26.ir exposes live status via `time_elapsed` + `finished`. `useTodayMatches` polls adaptively: 30 s during `IN_PLAY`/`PAUSED`, 60 s within 15 min of kickoff, 5 min otherwise, plus refetch on tab visibility.
- The serverless `/api/football/*` proxy adds a 30 s games cache + single-flight to absorb bursts. Team metadata (flags, names) is cached for the lifetime of the serverless instance.
- When `USE_MATCHES_MIRROR=true`, user-facing routes read from Supabase `matches_mirror`/`teams_mirror` (populated by cron). Default is live worldcup26.ir.

## Profile page (`/profile`) ‚Äî required content
1. **Account details:** name, email, joined date.
2. **Bet Summary:**
   - üèÜ Tournament Winner
   - ‚öΩ Top Scorer
   - üéØ Top Assist
   - üìù Match Predictions ‚Äî number of matches the user has placed a prediction on.
3. **üìã My Match Predictions** ‚Äî list every match the user predicted, formatted as `Mexico vs South Africa  0‚Äì0`. Sort by match kickoff date.
4. **üéØ Tournament Bets** ‚Äî editable **only before** the tournament starts (Jun 11, 2026 19:00 UTC opening kickoff). After kickoff, render as locked / read-only.
   - üèÖ **World Cup Winner** ‚Äî dropdown of all national teams playing in the World Cup (live football API).
   - ‚öΩ **Top Scorer** ‚Äî dropdown from a fixed list (`TOP_SCORERS_LIST`, supplied by user; leave placeholder until then).
   - üéØ **Top Assist** ‚Äî dropdown from a fixed list (`TOP_ASSISTS_LIST`, supplied by user; leave placeholder until then).

## General principles
- Keep it simple ‚Äî avoid premature abstraction and extra dependencies.
- Reuse existing patterns: `AuthContext`, `serverApi`, the `useMatches` / `useTodayMatches` hooks, CSS modules.
- Never expose service-role keys or third-party API tokens to the browser.
- Validate inputs both client-side and server-side.
- When in doubt, ask the user before introducing a new library or architectural change.

