## How requests flow
| URL | In production (Vercel) | In dev (`npm run dev:all`) |
|---|---|---|
| `/` (and any non-API route) | static SPA from `dist/`, falls back to `index.html` via `vercel.json` rewrite | Vite dev server on `:5173` |
| `/api/*` | `api/index.js` serverless function ‚Üí Express app | Vite proxies to `:3000` running `dev-server.cjs` (same Express app) |

The Express app inside the function is mounted **with the `/api/` prefix** because Vercel forwards `req.url` with the prefix intact. Local dev keeps full parity.

**Vercel Cron:** `vercel.json` schedules `GET /api/cron/refresh-matches` every minute ‚Üí `refreshMirror()` writes `matches_mirror` + `teams_mirror`.

