## Environment variables
Set these in `.env` locally and in **Vercel project settings** for production. See `.env.example` for the full list.

| Name | Where | Required | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `SUPABASE_URL` | server | yes | |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | server | yes | |
| `JWT_SECRET` | server | yes | |
| `WC26_API_BASE_URL` | server | optional | defaults to `https://worldcup26.ir` |
| `WC26_API_EMAIL` | server | optional | upstream JWT service account |
| `WC26_API_PASSWORD` | server | optional | paired with `WC26_API_EMAIL` |
| `RESEND_API_KEY` | server | optional | no-op when blank |
| `RESEND_FROM_EMAIL` | server | optional | |
| `CLIENT_ORIGIN` | server | optional | locks CORS in prod |
| `USE_MATCHES_MIRROR` | server | optional | exact `"true"` ‚Üí read Supabase mirror |
| `CRON_SECRET` | server | optional | Bearer auth for Vercel Cron |
| `VITE_API_BASE_URL` | browser | optional | leave blank for same-origin `/api` |
| `VITE_SIMULATION_MODE` | both | optional | exact `"true"` ‚Üí in-memory demo data; read-only writes |

The browser **must never** see `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `WC26_API_PASSWORD`, `RESEND_API_KEY`, `JWT_SECRET`, or `CRON_SECRET`.

**Simulation mode:** When `VITE_SIMULATION_MODE=true`, backend serves mock data from `api/mock/worldCupSimulation.js`; all writes return 403. Frontend shows orange `SimulationBanner`. **Never set in production Vercel env** ‚Äî Vite bakes it into the build.

## Conventions every agent must follow

### Frontend
- All user-visible text goes through `useTranslation()` and lives in both `locales/en.json` AND `locales/he.json`. **Never** add a key to one without the other.
- Use logical CSS properties (`margin-inline-start/end`, `padding-inline-*`, `inset-inline-*`) so layouts flip cleanly in RTL. Avoid `margin-left/right` unless the side is intentionally physical (safe-area insets).
- Date/time formatting: `toLocaleDateString(locale, ‚Ä¶)` where `locale = i18n.resolvedLanguage === 'he' ? 'he-IL' : 'en-GB'`.
- Reuse: `AuthContext` (auth + users + scores), `serverApi` (axios with cookie auth + 401 handler), `useMatches` (session-cached schedule), `useTodayMatches` (smart polling).
- CSS Modules only ‚Äî no global classes (except `index.css` utilities), no Tailwind, no styled-components.
- Mantine components must work in RTL ‚Äî `MantineDirectionSync` already wires this; do not duplicate.
- Prefer editing `*.module.css` over JSX when doing UI-only work. Do not refactor unrelated files.

### Backend (Vercel functions)
- Files under `api/` are **CommonJS** (`require`/`module.exports`) ‚Äî `api/package.json` enforces this. Files under `src/` are ESM.
- Never call `createClient()` at module load. Use the lazy `supabase` Proxy from `api/_lib/supabase.js`.
- Every worldcup26.ir call MUST go through `wc26Request()` / `fetchUpstream()` in `api/_lib/football.js` so it shares the cache + single-flight registry. Never call `axios.get('https://worldcup26.ir/...')` directly from a route file.
- All external football data is normalized server-side via `transformGame` / `transformTeam` in `api/_lib/football.js`. **Route handlers never leak upstream field names (`home_team_id`, `time_elapsed`, etc.) to the browser** ‚Äî the frontend speaks the internal shape.
- Errors: throw or `next(err)`. The central handler in `_lib/errorHandler.js` sanitizes DB errors to a generic message; route-level errors with `err.status` pass through.
- Auth: `requireAuth` first, `requireAdmin` second, `requireFreshAdmin` for sensitive admin mutations (re-validates role from DB).
- Users can only mutate their own data unless admin ‚Äî every protected route enforces this server-side, even if the client already filtered.
- Mirror writes ONLY via `refreshMirror()` in `api/_lib/mirrorRefresh.js` ‚Äî called by cron and admin backfill. Never write mirror tables from user-facing routes.

### PWA
- Icons live in `public/`; the manifest is generated by `vite-plugin-pwa` from `vite.config.js`. To regenerate after replacing the source icon, run:
  ```
  powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/resize-icons.ps1
  ```
- The service worker explicitly excludes `/api/*` from navigation fallback, so dynamic backend calls always reach the network.

### Adding a route
1. Backend: append to (or create) the relevant file under `api/_routes/` and mount it in `api/_app.js`. Always pass `requireAuth` (and `requireAdmin` where appropriate).
2. Frontend: add a method on `serverApi`, then call it from a hook or component. Translation keys for new UI strings go in BOTH locale files.
3. Document the new endpoint in this control file's REST surface table.

## Known follow-ups (pick these up as they unblock)
- **`TOP_SCORERS_LIST` and `TOP_ASSISTS_LIST`** in `src/utils/constants.js` may still have placeholder tiers. Profile dropdowns AND `TopScorersPage` read from these lists. The owner supplies final names; agents must not invent them.
- Knockout bracket slots in worldcup26.ir may show placeholder labels (`Winner Match 74`, etc.) until teams are determined. `AllGamesPage` shows an empty state if no events returned.
- **Match IDs are worldcup26 `1`‚Äì`104`**, not TheSportsDB `idEvent` values. Any predictions stored under old IDs will not join to the new schedule.
- The admin must run **POST `/api/scores/recalculate`** after tournament end with `{ tournamentWinner, actualTopScorer, actualTopAssist }` to award the 15/5/5 bonus points. The HomePage admin panel exposes this UI.
- **`USE_MATCHES_MIRROR` rollout:** verify via `GET /api/admin/mirror-compare` (all categories match) before enabling in production.

## Hard "do not"s
- Do **not** re-introduce the deleted `server/` Express folder or any non-Vercel host.
- Do **not** install `bcrypt` (native) ‚Äî the project uses `bcryptjs`.
- Do **not** hard-code English (or Hebrew) strings in JSX. Use `t('key')`.
- Do **not** call worldcup26.ir from the browser ‚Äî always go through `/api/football/*`. The frontend has no business knowing upstream field names like `home_team_id` or `time_elapsed`.
- Do **not** re-introduce a generic pass-through proxy at `/api/football/*`. The proxy is intentionally narrow: a handful of typed, normalized endpoints so the upstream schema can be swapped without touching the frontend.
- Do **not** invent player names for `TOP_SCORERS_LIST` / `TOP_ASSISTS_LIST`. The owner supplies them.
- Do **not** add a new top-level dependency without first checking whether existing libs (Mantine, axios, react-router) already cover the need.
- Do **not** change scoring logic, auth logic, database schema, API behavior, cron behavior, or prediction locking rules unless the owner explicitly asks.
- Do **not** set `VITE_SIMULATION_MODE=true` in production Vercel env.
- Do **not** edit the front-matter `description` of this file or the "Your role" / "What this app is" sections without explicit owner approval ‚Äî those are product intent, not implementation detail.
